'''SASI (Schools Administrative Student Information)''' or '''SASI Student Information System''' is a [[computer program]] developed by Macro Educational Computer Systems, who was acquired by National Computer Systems (NCS) and NCS was acquired by Pearson in 1997. The [[cross-platform]] system provides administrators and educators with access to student demographics, attendance, schedules, discipline, grades, extended test histories, and state reporting codes.<ref>[http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0EIN/is_2003_Sept_22/ai_108015808 New White Paper Finds That Technology-Based Student Information Systems Are Essential If Schools Hope to Reach NCLB Reporting Goals]</ref><ref>[https://www.questia.com/googleScholar.qst;jsessionid=JdtXjz1cPWDZ2Dng428H6cMlvTPsRsp8tsv1hjGP14BGCg6yP5q3!625449129?docId=5000441296 SASIxp: This SIS Has Personality. ''Technological Horizons In Education'']</ref> Features of SASI include SASIxp, InteGrade Pro, classroomXP, and Parent Access. In 2003, more than 16,000 schools nationwide used the software.<ref>[http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-23665322_ITM NCLB And AYP Reporting Tools Featured in New SASIxp 5.5 Student Information System. Business Wire]</ref>
